84 bool Map::ExistMap(uint32 mapid, int gx, int gy)
85 {
86  int len = sWorld->GetDataPath().length() + strlen("maps/%03u%02u%02u.map") + 1;
87  char* tmp = new char[len];
88  snprintf(tmp, len, (char*)(sWorld->GetDataPath() + "maps/%03u%02u%02u.map").c_str(), mapid, gx, gy);
89 
90  bool ret = false;
91  FILE* pf = fopen(tmp, "rb");
92 
93  if (!pf)
94  LOG_ERROR("maps", "Map file '%s': does not exist!", tmp);
95  else
96  {
97  map_fileheader header;
98  if (fread(&header, sizeof(header), 1, pf) == 1)
99  {
100  if (header.mapMagic != MapMagic.asUInt || header.versionMagic != MapVersionMagic)
101  {
102  LOG_ERROR("maps", "Map file '%s' is from an incompatible map version (%.*u v%u), %.*s v%u is expected. Please pull your source, recompile tools and recreate maps using the updated mapextractor, then replace your old map files with new files.",
103  tmp, 4, header.mapMagic, header.versionMagic, 4, MapMagic.asChar, MapVersionMagic);
104  }
105 
106  else
107  ret = true;
108  }
109  fclose(pf);
110  }
111  delete [] tmp;
112  return ret;
113 }

134 void Map::LoadMMap(int gx, int gy)
135 {
136  if (!DisableMgr::IsPathfindingEnabled(this)) // pussywizard
137  return;
138 
139  int mmapLoadResult = MMAP::MMapFactory::createOrGetMMapMgr()->loadMap(GetId(), gx, gy);
140  switch (mmapLoadResult)
141  {
142  case MMAP::MMAP_LOAD_RESULT_OK:
143  LOG_DEBUG("maps", "MMAP loaded name:%s, id:%d, x:%d, y:%d (vmap rep.: x:%d, y:%d)", GetMapName(), GetId(), gx, gy, gx, gy);
144  break;
145  case MMAP::MMAP_LOAD_RESULT_ERROR:
146  LOG_DEBUG("maps", "Could not load MMAP name:%s, id:%d, x:%d, y:%d (vmap rep.: x:%d, y:%d)", GetMapName(), GetId(), gx, gy, gx, gy);
147  break;
148  case MMAP::MMAP_LOAD_RESULT_IGNORED:
149  LOG_DEBUG("maps", "Ignored MMAP name:%s, id:%d, x:%d, y:%d (vmap rep.: x:%d, y:%d)", GetMapName(), GetId(), gx, gy, gx, gy);
150  break;
151  }

172 void Map::LoadMap(int gx, int gy, bool reload)
173 {
174  if (i_InstanceId != 0)
175  {
176  if (GridMaps[gx][gy])
177  return;
178 
179  // load grid map for base map
180  m_parentMap->EnsureGridCreated(GridCoord(63 - gx, 63 - gy));
181 
182  GridMaps[gx][gy] = m_parentMap->GridMaps[gx][gy];
183  return;
184  }
185 
186  if (GridMaps[gx][gy] && !reload)
187  return;
188 
189  //map already load, delete it before reloading (Is it necessary? Do we really need the ability the reload maps during runtime?)
190  if (GridMaps[gx][gy])
191  {
192  LOG_DEBUG("maps", "Unloading previously loaded map %u before reloading.", GetId());
193  sScriptMgr->OnUnloadGridMap(this, GridMaps[gx][gy], gx, gy);
194 
195  delete (GridMaps[gx][gy]);
196  GridMaps[gx][gy] = nullptr;
197  }
198 
199  // map file name
200  char* tmp = nullptr;
201  int len = sWorld->GetDataPath().length() + strlen("maps/%03u%02u%02u.map") + 1;
202  tmp = new char[len];
203  snprintf(tmp, len, (char*)(sWorld->GetDataPath() + "maps/%03u%02u%02u.map").c_str(), GetId(), gx, gy);
204  LOG_DEBUG("maps", "Loading map %s", tmp);
205  // loading data
206  GridMaps[gx][gy] = new GridMap();
207  if (!GridMaps[gx][gy]->loadData(tmp))
208  {
209  LOG_ERROR("maps", "Error loading map file: \n %s\n", tmp);
210  }
211  delete [] tmp;
212 
213  sScriptMgr->OnLoadGridMap(this, GridMaps[gx][gy], gx, gy);
214 }

309 template<>
310 void Map::AddToGrid(Corpse* obj, Cell const& cell)
311 {
312  NGridType* grid = getNGrid(cell.GridX(), cell.GridY());
313  // Corpses are a special object type - they can be added to grid via a call to AddToMap
314  // or loaded through ObjectGridLoader.
315  // Both corpses loaded from database and these freshly generated by Player::CreateCoprse are added to _corpsesByCell
316  // ObjectGridLoader loads all corpses from _corpsesByCell even if they were already added to grid before it was loaded
317  // so we need to explicitly check it here (Map::AddToGrid is only called from Player::BuildPlayerRepop, not from ObjectGridLoader)
318  // to avoid failing an assertion in GridObject::AddToGrid
319  if (grid->isGridObjectDataLoaded())
320  {
321  if (obj->IsWorldObject())
322  grid->GetGridType(cell.CellX(), cell.CellY()).AddWorldObject(obj);
323  else
324  grid->GetGridType(cell.CellX(), cell.CellY()).AddGridObject(obj);
325  }

333 template<>
334 void Map::SwitchGridContainers(Creature* obj, bool on)
335 {
336  ASSERT(!obj->IsPermanentWorldObject());
337  CellCoord p = Acore::ComputeCellCoord(obj->GetPositionX(), obj->GetPositionY());
338  if (!p.IsCoordValid())
339  {
340  LOG_ERROR("maps", "Map::SwitchGridContainers: Object %s has invalid coordinates X:%f Y:%f grid cell [%u:%u]",
341  obj->GetGUID().ToString().c_str(), obj->GetPositionX(), obj->GetPositionY(), p.x_coord, p.y_coord);
342  return;
343  }
344 
345  Cell cell(p);
346  if (!IsGridLoaded(GridCoord(cell.data.Part.grid_x, cell.data.Part.grid_y)))
347  return;
348 
349  LOG_DEBUG("maps", "Switch object %s from grid[%u, %u] %d", obj->GetGUID().ToString().c_str(), cell.GridX(), cell.GridY(), on);
350  NGridType* ngrid = getNGrid(cell.GridX(), cell.GridY());
351  ASSERT(ngrid != nullptr);
352 
353  GridType& grid = ngrid->GetGridType(cell.CellX(), cell.CellY());
354 
355  obj->RemoveFromGrid(); //This step is not really necessary but we want to do ASSERT in remove/add
356 
357  if (on)
358  {
359  grid.AddWorldObject(obj);
360  AddWorldObject(obj);
361  }
362  else
363  {
364  grid.AddGridObject(obj);
365  RemoveWorldObject(obj);
366  }
367 
368  obj->m_isTempWorldObject = on;
369 }

545 template<class T>
546 bool Map::AddToMap(T* obj, bool checkTransport)
547 {
548  //TODO: Needs clean up. An object should not be added to map twice.
549  if (obj->IsInWorld())
550  {
551  ASSERT(obj->IsInGrid());
552  obj->UpdateObjectVisibility(true);
553  return true;
554  }
555 
556  CellCoord cellCoord = Acore::ComputeCellCoord(obj->GetPositionX(), obj->GetPositionY());
557  //It will create many problems (including crashes) if an object is not added to grid after creation
558  //The correct way to fix it is to make AddToMap return false and delete the object if it is not added to grid
559  //But now AddToMap is used in too many places, I will just see how many ASSERT failures it will cause
560  ASSERT(cellCoord.IsCoordValid());
561  if (!cellCoord.IsCoordValid())
562  {
563  LOG_ERROR("maps", "Map::AddToMap: Object %s has invalid coordinates X:%f Y:%f grid cell [%u:%u]",
564  obj->GetGUID().ToString().c_str(), obj->GetPositionX(), obj->GetPositionY(), cellCoord.x_coord, cellCoord.y_coord);
565  return false; //Should delete object
566  }
567 
568  Cell cell(cellCoord);
569  if (obj->isActiveObject())
570  EnsureGridLoaded(cell);
571  else
572  EnsureGridCreated(GridCoord(cell.GridX(), cell.GridY()));
573 
574  AddToGrid(obj, cell);
575 
576  //Must already be set before AddToMap. Usually during obj->Create.
577  //obj->SetMap(this);
578  obj->AddToWorld();
579 
580  if (checkTransport)
581  if (!(obj->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_GAMEOBJECT && obj->ToGameObject()->IsTransport())) // dont add transport to transport ;d
582  if (Transport* transport = GetTransportForPos(obj->GetPhaseMask(), obj->GetPositionX(), obj->GetPositionY(), obj->GetPositionZ(), obj))
583  transport->AddPassenger(obj, true);
584 
585  InitializeObject(obj);
586 
587  if (obj->isActiveObject())
588  AddToActive(obj);
589 
590  //something, such as vehicle, needs to be update immediately
591  //also, trigger needs to cast spell, if not update, cannot see visual
592  obj->UpdateObjectVisibility(true);
593 
594  // Xinef: little hack for vehicles, accessories have to be added after visibility update so they wont fall off the vehicle, moved from Creature::AIM_Initialize
595  // Initialize vehicle, this is done only for summoned npcs, DB creatures are handled by grid loaders
596  if (obj->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_UNIT)
597  if (Vehicle* vehicle = obj->ToCreature()->GetVehicleKit())
598  vehicle->Reset();
599  return true;
600 }

610  if (!cellCoord.IsCoordValid())
611  {
612  LOG_ERROR("maps", "Map::Add: Object %s has invalid coordinates X:%f Y:%f grid cell [%u:%u]",
613  obj->GetGUID().ToString().c_str(), obj->GetPositionX(), obj->GetPositionY(), cellCoord.x_coord, cellCoord.y_coord);
614  return false; //Should delete object
615  }
616 
617  Cell cell(cellCoord);
618  if (obj->isActiveObject())
619  EnsureGridLoaded(cell);
620 
621  obj->AddToWorld();
622 
623  if (obj->isActiveObject())
624  AddToActive(obj);
625 
626  _transports.insert(obj);
627 
628  // Broadcast creation to players
629  if (!GetPlayers().isEmpty())
630  {
631  for (Map::PlayerList::const_iterator itr = GetPlayers().begin(); itr != GetPlayers().end(); ++itr)
632  {
633  if (itr->GetSource()->GetTransport() != obj)
634  {
635  UpdateData data;
636  obj->BuildCreateUpdateBlockForPlayer(&data, itr->GetSource());
637  WorldPacket packet;
638  data.BuildPacket(&packet);
639  itr->GetSource()->SendDirectMessage(&packet);
640  }
641  }
642  }
643 
644  return true;
645 }

648 {
649  return (getNGrid(p.x_coord, p.y_coord) && isGridObjectDataLoaded(p.x_coord, p.y_coord));

652 void Map::VisitNearbyCellsOfPlayer(Player* player, TypeContainerVisitor<Acore::ObjectUpdater, GridTypeMapContainer>& gridVisitor,
653  TypeContainerVisitor<Acore::ObjectUpdater, WorldTypeMapContainer>& worldVisitor,
654  TypeContainerVisitor<Acore::ObjectUpdater, GridTypeMapContainer>& largeGridVisitor,
655  TypeContainerVisitor<Acore::ObjectUpdater, WorldTypeMapContainer>& largeWorldVisitor)
656 {
657  // check for valid position
658  if (!player->IsPositionValid())
659  return;
660 
661  // check normal grid activation range of the player
662  VisitNearbyCellsOf(player, gridVisitor, worldVisitor, largeGridVisitor, largeWorldVisitor);
663 
664  // check maximum visibility distance for large creatures
665  CellArea area = Cell::CalculateCellArea(player->GetPositionX(), player->GetPositionY(), MAX_VISIBILITY_DISTANCE);
666 
667  for (uint32 x = area.low_bound.x_coord; x <= area.high_bound.x_coord; ++x)
668  {
669  for (uint32 y = area.low_bound.y_coord; y <= area.high_bound.y_coord; ++y)
670  {
671  // marked cells are those that have been visited
672  // don't visit the same cell twice
673  uint32 cell_id = (y * TOTAL_NUMBER_OF_CELLS_PER_MAP) + x;
674  if (isCellMarkedLarge(cell_id))
675  continue;
676 
677  markCellLarge(cell_id);
678  CellCoord pair(x, y);
679  Cell cell(pair);
680 
681  Visit(cell, largeGridVisitor);
682  Visit(cell, largeWorldVisitor);
683  }
684  }
685 }
686 
687 void Map::VisitNearbyCellsOf(WorldObject* obj, TypeContainerVisitor<Acore::ObjectUpdater, GridTypeMapContainer>& gridVisitor,
688  TypeContainerVisitor<Acore::ObjectUpdater, WorldTypeMapContainer>& worldVisitor,
689  TypeContainerVisitor<Acore::ObjectUpdater, GridTypeMapContainer>& largeGridVisitor,
690  TypeContainerVisitor<Acore::ObjectUpdater, WorldTypeMapContainer>& largeWorldVisitor)
691 {
692  // Check for valid position
693  if (!obj->IsPositionValid())
694  return;
695 
696  if (obj->GetGridActivationRange() <= 0.0f) // pussywizard: gameobjects for example are on active lists, but range is equal to 0 (they just prevent grid unloading)
697  return;
698 
699  // Update mobs/objects in ALL visible cells around object!
700  CellArea area = Cell::CalculateCellArea(obj->GetPositionX(), obj->GetPositionY(), obj->GetGridActivationRange());
701 
702  for (uint32 x = area.low_bound.x_coord; x <= area.high_bound.x_coord; ++x)
703  {
704  for (uint32 y = area.low_bound.y_coord; y <= area.high_bound.y_coord; ++y)
705  {
706  // marked cells are those that have been visited
707  // don't visit the same cell twice
708  uint32 cell_id = (y * TOTAL_NUMBER_OF_CELLS_PER_MAP) + x;
709  if (isCellMarked(cell_id))
710  continue;
711 
712  markCell(cell_id);
713  CellCoord pair(x, y);
714  Cell cell(pair);
715  //cell.SetNoCreate(); // in mmaps this is missing
716 
717  Visit(cell, gridVisitor);
718  Visit(cell, worldVisitor);
719 
720  if (!isCellMarkedLarge(cell_id))
721  {
722  markCellLarge(cell_id);
723  Visit(cell, largeGridVisitor);
724  Visit(cell, largeWorldVisitor);
725  }
726  }
727  }
728 }

730 void Map::Update(const uint32 t_diff, const uint32 s_diff, bool /*thread*/)
731 {
732  if (t_diff)
733  _dynamicTree.update(t_diff);
734 
736  for (m_mapRefIter = m_mapRefMgr.begin(); m_mapRefIter != m_mapRefMgr.end(); ++m_mapRefIter)
737  {
738  Player* player = m_mapRefIter->GetSource();
739  if (player && player->IsInWorld())
740  {
741  //player->Update(t_diff);
742  WorldSession* session = player->GetSession();
743  MapSessionFilter updater(session);
744  session->Update(s_diff, updater);
745  }
746  }
747 
748  if (!t_diff)
749  {
750  for (m_mapRefIter = m_mapRefMgr.begin(); m_mapRefIter != m_mapRefMgr.end(); ++m_mapRefIter)
751  {
752  Player* player = m_mapRefIter->GetSource();
753 
754  if (!player || !player->IsInWorld())
755  continue;
756 
757  // update players at tick
758  player->Update(s_diff);
759  }
760 
761  HandleDelayedVisibility();
762  return;
763  }
764 
766  resetMarkedCells();
767  resetMarkedCellsLarge();
768 
769  Acore::ObjectUpdater updater(t_diff, false);
770 
771  // for creature
772  TypeContainerVisitor<Acore::ObjectUpdater, GridTypeMapContainer > grid_object_update(updater);
773  // for pets
774  TypeContainerVisitor<Acore::ObjectUpdater, WorldTypeMapContainer > world_object_update(updater);
775 
776  // for large creatures
777  Acore::ObjectUpdater largeObjectUpdater(t_diff, true);
778  TypeContainerVisitor<Acore::ObjectUpdater, GridTypeMapContainer > grid_large_object_update(largeObjectUpdater);
779  TypeContainerVisitor<Acore::ObjectUpdater, WorldTypeMapContainer > world_large_object_update(largeObjectUpdater);
780 
781  // pussywizard: container for far creatures in combat with players
782  std::vector<Creature*> updateList;
783  updateList.reserve(10);
784 
785  // non-player active objects, increasing iterator in the loop in case of object removal
786  for (m_activeNonPlayersIter = m_activeNonPlayers.begin(); m_activeNonPlayersIter != m_activeNonPlayers.end();)
787  {
788  WorldObject* obj = *m_activeNonPlayersIter;
789  ++m_activeNonPlayersIter;
790 
791  if (!obj || !obj->IsInWorld())
792  continue;
793 
794  VisitNearbyCellsOf(obj, grid_object_update, world_object_update, grid_large_object_update, world_large_object_update);
795  }
796 
797  // the player iterator is stored in the map object
798  // to make sure calls to Map::Remove don't invalidate it
799  for (m_mapRefIter = m_mapRefMgr.begin(); m_mapRefIter != m_mapRefMgr.end(); ++m_mapRefIter)
800  {
801  Player* player = m_mapRefIter->GetSource();
802 
803  if (!player || !player->IsInWorld())
804  continue;
805 
806  // update players at tick
807  player->Update(s_diff);
808 
809  VisitNearbyCellsOfPlayer(player, grid_object_update, world_object_update, grid_large_object_update, world_large_object_update);
810 
811  // If player is using far sight, visit that object too
812  if (WorldObject* viewPoint = player->GetViewpoint())
813  {
814  if (Creature* viewCreature = viewPoint->ToCreature())
815  {
816  VisitNearbyCellsOf(viewCreature, grid_object_update, world_object_update, grid_large_object_update, world_large_object_update);
817  }
818  else if (DynamicObject* viewObject = viewPoint->ToDynObject())
819  {
820  VisitNearbyCellsOf(viewObject, grid_object_update, world_object_update, grid_large_object_update, world_large_object_update);
821  }
822  }
823 
824  // handle updates for creatures in combat with player and are more than X yards away
825  if (player->IsInCombat())
826  {
827  updateList.clear();
828  float rangeSq = player->GetGridActivationRange() - 1.0f;
829  rangeSq = rangeSq * rangeSq;
830  HostileReference* ref = player->getHostileRefMgr().getFirst();
831  while (ref)
832  {
833  if (Unit* unit = ref->GetSource()->GetOwner())
834  if (Creature* cre = unit->ToCreature())
835  if (cre->FindMap() == player->FindMap() && cre->GetExactDist2dSq(player) > rangeSq)
836  updateList.push_back(cre);
837  ref = ref->next();
838  }
839  for (std::vector<Creature*>::const_iterator itr = updateList.begin(); itr != updateList.end(); ++itr)
840  VisitNearbyCellsOf(*itr, grid_object_update, world_object_update, grid_large_object_update, world_large_object_update);
841  }
842  }
843 
844  for (_transportsUpdateIter = _transports.begin(); _transportsUpdateIter != _transports.end();) // pussywizard: transports updated after VisitNearbyCellsOf, grids around are loaded, everything ok
845  {
846  MotionTransport* transport = *_transportsUpdateIter;
847  ++_transportsUpdateIter;
848 
849  if (!transport->IsInWorld())
850  continue;
851 
852  transport->Update(t_diff);
853  }
854 
855  SendObjectUpdates();
856 
858  if (!m_scriptSchedule.empty())
859  {
860  i_scriptLock = true;
861  ScriptsProcess();
862  i_scriptLock = false;
863  }
864 
865  MoveAllCreaturesInMoveList();
866  MoveAllGameObjectsInMoveList();
867  MoveAllDynamicObjectsInMoveList();
868 
869  HandleDelayedVisibility();
870 
871  sScriptMgr->OnMapUpdate(this, t_diff);
872 
873  METRIC_VALUE("map_creatures", uint64(GetObjectsStore().Size<Creature>()),
874  METRIC_TAG("map_id", std::to_string(GetId())),
875  METRIC_TAG("map_instanceid", std::to_string(GetInstanceId())));
876 
877  METRIC_VALUE("map_gameobjects", uint64(GetObjectsStore().Size<GameObject>()),
878  METRIC_TAG("map_id", std::to_string(GetId())),
879  METRIC_TAG("map_instanceid", std::to_string(GetInstanceId())));
880 }

951 void Map::RemoveFromMap(MotionTransport* obj, bool remove)
952 {

955  RemoveFromActive(obj);
956 
957  Map::PlayerList const& players = GetPlayers();
958  if (!players.isEmpty())

975  ++_transportsUpdateIter;

980

1203 bool Map::UnloadGrid(NGridType& ngrid)
1204 {
1205  // pussywizard: UnloadGrid only done when whole map is unloaded, no need to worry about moving npcs between grids, etc.
1206 
1207  const uint32 x = ngrid.getX();
1208  const uint32 y = ngrid.getY();
1209 
1210  {
1211  ObjectGridCleaner worker;
1212  TypeContainerVisitor<ObjectGridCleaner, GridTypeMapContainer> visitor(worker);
1213  ngrid.VisitAllGrids(visitor);
1214  }
1215 
1216  RemoveAllObjectsInRemoveList();
1217 
1218  {
1219  ObjectGridUnloader worker;
1220  TypeContainerVisitor<ObjectGridUnloader, GridTypeMapContainer> visitor(worker);
1221  ngrid.VisitAllGrids(visitor);
1222  }
1223 
1224  ASSERT(i_objectsToRemove.empty());
1225 
1226  delete &ngrid;
1227  setNGrid(nullptr, x, y);
1228 
1229  int gx = (MAX_NUMBER_OF_GRIDS - 1) - x;
1230  int gy = (MAX_NUMBER_OF_GRIDS - 1) - y;
1231 
1232  if (i_InstanceId == 0)
1233  {
1234  if (GridMaps[gx][gy])
1235  {
1236  GridMaps[gx][gy]->unloadData();
1237  delete GridMaps[gx][gy];
1238  }
1239  // x and y are swapped
1240  VMAP::VMapFactory::createOrGetVMapMgr()->unloadMap(GetId(), gx, gy);
1241  MMAP::MMapFactory::createOrGetMMapMgr()->unloadMap(GetId(), gx, gy);
1242  }
1243 
1244  GridMaps[gx][gy] = nullptr;
1245 
1246  LOG_DEBUG("maps", "Unloading grid[%u, %u] for map %u finished", x, y, GetId());
1247  return true;
1248 }

1250 void Map::RemoveAllPlayers()
1251 {
1252  if (HavePlayers())
1253  {
1254  for (MapRefMgr::iterator itr = m_mapRefMgr.begin(); itr != m_mapRefMgr.end(); ++itr)
1255  {
1256  Player* player = itr->GetSource();
1257  if (!player->IsBeingTeleportedFar())

1345 bool GridMap::loadData(char* filename)
1346 {
1347  // Unload old data if exist
1348  unloadData();
1349 
1350  map_fileheader header;
1351  // Not return error if file not found
1352  FILE* in = fopen(filename, "rb");
1353  if (!in)
1354  return true;
1355 
1356  if (fread(&header, sizeof(header), 1, in) != 1)
1357  {
1358  fclose(in);
1359  return false;
1360  }
1361 
1362  if (header.mapMagic == MapMagic.asUInt && header.versionMagic == MapVersionMagic)
1363  {
1364  // loadup area data
1365  if (header.areaMapOffset && !loadAreaData(in, header.areaMapOffset, header.areaMapSize))
1366  {
1367  LOG_ERROR("maps", "Error loading map area data\n");
1368  fclose(in);
1369  return false;
1370  }
1371  // loadup height data
1372  if (header.heightMapOffset && !loadHeightData(in, header.heightMapOffset, header.heightMapSize))
1373  {
1374  LOG_ERROR("maps", "Error loading map height data\n");
1375  fclose(in);
1376  return false;
1377  }
1378  // loadup liquid data
1379  if (header.liquidMapOffset && !loadLiquidData(in, header.liquidMapOffset, header.liquidMapSize))
1380  {
1381  LOG_ERROR("maps", "Error loading map liquids data\n");
1382  fclose(in);
1383  return false;
1384  }
1385  // loadup holes data (if any. check header.holesOffset)
1386  if (header.holesSize && !loadHolesData(in, header.holesOffset, header.holesSize))
1387  {
1388  LOG_ERROR("maps", "Error loading map holes data\n");
1389  fclose(in);
1390  return false;
1391  }
1392  fclose(in);
1393  return true;
1394  }
1395  LOG_ERROR("maps", "Map file '%s' is from an incompatible clientversion. Please recreate using the mapextractor.", filename);
1396  fclose(in);
1397  return false;
1398 }

1423 bool GridMap::loadAreaData(FILE* in, uint32 offset, uint32 /*size*/)
1424 {
1425  map_areaHeader header;
1426  fseek(in, offset, SEEK_SET);
1427 
1428  if (fread(&header, sizeof(header), 1, in) != 1 || header.fourcc != MapAreaMagic.asUInt)
1429  return false;
1430 
1431  _gridArea = header.gridArea;
1432  if (!(header.flags & MAP_AREA_NO_AREA))
1433  {
1434  _areaMap = new uint16 [16 * 16];
1435  if (fread(_areaMap, sizeof(uint16), 16 * 16, in) != 16 * 16)
1436  return false;
1437  }
1438  return true;

1441 bool GridMap::loadHeightData(FILE* in, uint32 offset, uint32 /*size*/)
1442 {
1443  map_heightHeader header;
1444  fseek(in, offset, SEEK_SET);
1445 
1446  if (fread(&header, sizeof(header), 1, in) != 1 || header.fourcc != MapHeightMagic.asUInt)
1447  return false;
1448 
1449  _gridHeight = header.gridHeight;
1450  if (!(header.flags & MAP_HEIGHT_NO_HEIGHT))
1451  {
1452  if ((header.flags & MAP_HEIGHT_AS_INT16))
1453  {
1454  m_uint16_V9 = new uint16 [129 * 129];
1455  m_uint16_V8 = new uint16 [128 * 128];
1456  if (fread(m_uint16_V9, sizeof(uint16), 129 * 129, in) != 129 * 129 ||
1457  fread(m_uint16_V8, sizeof(uint16), 128 * 128, in) != 128 * 128)
1458  return false;
1459  _gridIntHeightMultiplier = (header.gridMaxHeight - header.gridHeight) / 65535;
1460  _gridGetHeight = &GridMap::getHeightFromUint16;
1461  }
1462  else if ((header.flags & MAP_HEIGHT_AS_INT8))
1463  {
1464  m_uint8_V9 = new uint8 [129 * 129];
1465  m_uint8_V8 = new uint8 [128 * 128];
1466  if (fread(m_uint8_V9, sizeof(uint8), 129 * 129, in) != 129 * 129 ||
1467  fread(m_uint8_V8, sizeof(uint8), 128 * 128, in) != 128 * 128)
1468  return false;
1469  _gridIntHeightMultiplier = (header.gridMaxHeight - header.gridHeight) / 255;
1470  _gridGetHeight = &GridMap::getHeightFromUint8;
1471  }
1472  else
1473  {
1474  m_V9 = new float [129 * 129];
1475  m_V8 = new float [128 * 128];
1476  if (fread(m_V9, sizeof(float), 129 * 129, in) != 129 * 129 ||
1477  fread(m_V8, sizeof(float), 128 * 128, in) != 128 * 128)
1478  return false;
1479  _gridGetHeight = &GridMap::getHeightFromFloat;
1480  }
1481  }
1482  else
1483  _gridGetHeight = &GridMap::getHeightFromFlat;
1484 
1485  if (header.flags & MAP_HEIGHT_HAS_FLIGHT_BOUNDS)
1486  {
1487  _maxHeight = new int16[3 * 3];
1488  _minHeight = new int16[3 * 3];
1489  if (fread(_maxHeight, sizeof(int16), 3 * 3, in) != 3 * 3 ||
1490  fread(_minHeight, sizeof(int16), 3 * 3, in) != 3 * 3)
1491  return false;
1492  }
1493 
1494  return true;
1495 }

1560 float GridMap::getHeightFromFloat(float x, float y) const
1561 {
1562  if (!m_V8 || !m_V9)
1563  return _gridHeight;
1564 
1565  x = MAP_RESOLUTION * (32 - x / SIZE_OF_GRIDS);
1566  y = MAP_RESOLUTION * (32 - y / SIZE_OF_GRIDS);
1567 
1568  int x_int = (int)x;
1569  int y_int = (int)y;
1570  x -= x_int;
1571  y -= y_int;
1572  x_int &= (MAP_RESOLUTION - 1);
1573  y_int &= (MAP_RESOLUTION - 1);
1574 
1575  if (isHole(x_int, y_int))
1576  return INVALID_HEIGHT;
1577 
1578  // Height stored as: h5 - its v8 grid, h1-h4 - its v9 grid
1579  // +--------------> X
1580  // | h1-------h2 Coordinates is:
1581  // | | \ 1 / | h1 0, 0
1582  // | | \ / | h2 0, 1
1583  // | | 2 h5 3 | h3 1, 0
1584  // | | / \ | h4 1, 1
1585  // | | / 4 \ | h5 1/2, 1/2
1586  // | h3-------h4
1587  // V Y
1588  // For find height need
1589  // 1 - detect triangle
1590  // 2 - solve linear equation from triangle points
1591  // Calculate coefficients for solve h = a*x + b*y + c
1592 
1593  float a, b, c;
1594  // Select triangle:
1595  if (x + y < 1)
1596  {
1597  if (x > y)
1598  {
1599  // 1 triangle (h1, h2, h5 points)
1600  float h1 = m_V9[(x_int) * 129 + y_int];
1601  float h2 = m_V9[(x_int + 1) * 129 + y_int];
1602  float h5 = 2 * m_V8[x_int * 128 + y_int];
1603  a = h2 - h1;
1604  b = h5 - h1 - h2;
1605  c = h1;
1606  }
1607  else
1608  {
1609  // 2 triangle (h1, h3, h5 points)
1610  float h1 = m_V9[x_int * 129 + y_int ];
1611  float h3 = m_V9[x_int * 129 + y_int + 1];
1612  float h5 = 2 * m_V8[x_int * 128 + y_int];
1613  a = h5 - h1 - h3;
1614  b = h3 - h1;
1615  c = h1;
1616  }
1617  }
1618  else
1619  {
1620  if (x > y)
1621  {
1622  // 3 triangle (h2, h4, h5 points)
1623  float h2 = m_V9[(x_int + 1) * 129 + y_int ];
1624  float h4 = m_V9[(x_int + 1) * 129 + y_int + 1];
1625  float h5 = 2 * m_V8[x_int * 128 + y_int];
1626  a = h2 + h4 - h5;
1627  b = h4 - h2;
1628  c = h5 - h4;
1629  }
1630  else
1631  {
1632  // 4 triangle (h3, h4, h5 points)
1633  float h3 = m_V9[(x_int) * 129 + y_int + 1];
1634  float h4 = m_V9[(x_int + 1) * 129 + y_int + 1];
1635  float h5 = 2 * m_V8[x_int * 128 + y_int];
1636  a = h4 - h3;
1637  b = h3 + h4 - h5;
1638  c = h5 - h4;
1639  }
1640  }
1641  // Calculate height
1642  return a * x + b * y + c;
1643 }

1785 bool GridMap::isHole(int row, int col) const
1786 {
1787  if (!_holes)
1788  return false;
1789 
1790  int cellRow = row / 8; // 8 squares per cell
1791  int cellCol = col / 8;
1792  int holeRow = row % 8 / 2;
1793  int holeCol = (col - (cellCol * 8)) / 2;
1794 
1795  uint16 hole = _holes[cellRow * 16 + cellCol];
1796 
1797  return (hole & holetab_h[holeCol] & holetab_v[holeRow]) != 0;
1798 }

1800 float GridMap::getMinHeight(float x, float y) const
1801 {
1802  if (!_minHeight)
1803  return -500.0f;
1804 
1805  static uint32 const indices[] =
1806  {
1807  3, 0, 4,
1808  0, 1, 4,
1809  1, 2, 4,
1810  2, 5, 4,
1811  5, 8, 4,
1812  8, 7, 4,
1813  7, 6, 4,
1814  6, 3, 4
1815  };
1816 
1817  static float const boundGridCoords[] =
1818  {
1819  0.0f, 0.0f,
1820  0.0f, -266.66666f,
1821  0.0f, -533.33331f,
1822  -266.66666f, 0.0f,
1823  -266.66666f, -266.66666f,
1824  -266.66666f, -533.33331f,
1825  -533.33331f, 0.0f,
1826  -533.33331f, -266.66666f,
1827  -533.33331f, -533.33331f
1828  };
1829 
1830  Cell cell(x, y);
1831  float gx = x - (int32(cell.GridX()) - CENTER_GRID_ID + 1) * SIZE_OF_GRIDS;
1832  float gy = y - (int32(cell.GridY()) - CENTER_GRID_ID + 1) * SIZE_OF_GRIDS;
1833 
1834  uint32 quarterIndex = 0;
1835  if (cell.CellY() < MAX_NUMBER_OF_CELLS / 2)
1836  {
1837  if (cell.CellX() < MAX_NUMBER_OF_CELLS / 2)
1838  {
1839  quarterIndex = 4 + (gy > gx);
1840  }
1841  else
1842  quarterIndex = 2 + ((-SIZE_OF_GRIDS - gx) > gy);
1843  }
1844  else if (cell.CellX() < MAX_NUMBER_OF_CELLS / 2)
1845  {
1846  quarterIndex = 6 + ((-SIZE_OF_GRIDS - gx) <= gy);
1847  }
1848  else
1849  quarterIndex = gx > gy;
1850 
1851  quarterIndex *= 3;
1852 
1853  return G3D::Plane(
1854  G3D::Vector3(boundGridCoords[indices[quarterIndex + 0] * 2 + 0], boundGridCoords[indices[quarterIndex + 0] * 2 + 1], _minHeight[indices[quarterIndex + 0]]),
1855  G3D::Vector3(boundGridCoords[indices[quarterIndex + 1] * 2 + 0], boundGridCoords[indices[quarterIndex + 1] * 2 + 1], _minHeight[indices[quarterIndex + 1]]),
1856  G3D::Vector3(boundGridCoords[indices[quarterIndex + 2] * 2 + 0], boundGridCoords[indices[quarterIndex + 2] * 2 + 1], _minHeight[indices[quarterIndex + 2]])
1857  ).distance(G3D::Vector3(gx, gy, 0.0f));
1858 }

1864 
1865  x = MAP_RESOLUTION * (32 - x / SIZE_OF_GRIDS);
1866  y = MAP_RESOLUTION * (32 - y / SIZE_OF_GRIDS);
1867 
1868  int cx_int = ((int)x & (MAP_RESOLUTION - 1)) - _liquidOffY;
1869  int cy_int = ((int)y & (MAP_RESOLUTION - 1)) - _liquidOffX;
1870 
1871  if (cx_int < 0 || cx_int >= _liquidHeight)
1872  return INVALID_HEIGHT;
1873  if (cy_int < 0 || cy_int >= _liquidWidth)
1874  return INVALID_HEIGHT;
1875 
1876  return _liquidMap[cx_int * _liquidWidth + cy_int];
1877 }

1879 // Get water state on map
1880 inline LiquidData const GridMap::GetLiquidData(float x, float y, float z, float collisionHeight, uint8 ReqLiquidType) const
1881 {
1882  LiquidData liquidData;
1883 
1884  // Check water type (if no water return)
1885  if (_liquidType || _liquidFlags)
1886  {
1887  // Get cell
1888  float cx = MAP_RESOLUTION * (32 - x / SIZE_OF_GRIDS);
1889  float cy = MAP_RESOLUTION * (32 - y / SIZE_OF_GRIDS);
1890 
1891  int x_int = (int) cx & (MAP_RESOLUTION - 1);
1892  int y_int = (int) cy & (MAP_RESOLUTION - 1);
1893 
1894  // Check water type in cell
1895  int idx = (x_int >> 3) * 16 + (y_int >> 3);
1896  uint8 type = _liquidFlags ? _liquidFlags[idx] : _liquidType;
1897  uint32 entry = 0;
1898  if (_liquidEntry)
1899  {
1900  if (LiquidTypeEntry const* liquidEntry = sLiquidTypeStore.LookupEntry(_liquidEntry[idx]))
1901  {
1902  entry = liquidEntry->Id;
1903  type &= MAP_LIQUID_TYPE_DARK_WATER;
1904  uint32 liqTypeIdx = liquidEntry->Type;
1905  if (entry < 21)
1906  {
1907  if (AreaTableEntry const* area = sAreaTableStore.LookupEntry(getArea(x, y)))
1908  {
1909  uint32 overrideLiquid = area->LiquidTypeOverride[liquidEntry->Type];
1910  if (!overrideLiquid && area->zone)
1911  {
1912  area = sAreaTableStore.LookupEntry(area->zone);
1913  if (area)
1914  overrideLiquid = area->LiquidTypeOverride[liquidEntry->Type];
1915  }
1916 
1917  if (LiquidTypeEntry const* liq = sLiquidTypeStore.LookupEntry(overrideLiquid))
1918  {
1919  entry = overrideLiquid;
1920  liqTypeIdx = liq->Type;
1921  }
1922  }
1923  }
1924 
1925  type |= 1 << liqTypeIdx;
1926  }
1927  }
1928 
1929  // Check req liquid type mask
1930  if (type != 0 && (!ReqLiquidType || (ReqLiquidType & type) != 0))
1931  {
1932  // Check water level:
1933  // Check water height map
1934  int lx_int = x_int - _liquidOffY;
1935  int ly_int = y_int - _liquidOffX;
1936  if (lx_int >= 0 && lx_int < _liquidHeight && ly_int >= 0 && ly_int < _liquidWidth)
1937  {
1938  // Get water level
1939  float liquid_level = _liquidMap ? _liquidMap[lx_int * _liquidWidth + ly_int] : _liquidLevel;
1940  // Get ground level (sub 0.2 for fix some errors)
1941  float ground_level = getHeight(x, y);
1942 
1943  // Check water level and ground level
1944  if (liquid_level >= ground_level && z >= ground_level - 2)
1945  {
1946  // All ok in water -> store data
1947  liquidData.Entry = entry;
1948  liquidData.Flags = type;
1949  liquidData.Level = liquid_level;
1950  liquidData.DepthLevel = ground_level;
1951 
1952  // For speed check as int values
1953  float delta = liquid_level - z;
1954 
1955  if (delta > collisionHeight)
1956  liquidData.Status = LIQUID_MAP_UNDER_WATER;
1957  else if (delta > 0.2f)
1958  liquidData.Status = LIQUID_MAP_IN_WATER;
1959  else if (delta > -0.2f)
1960  liquidData.Status = LIQUID_MAP_WATER_WALK;
1961  else
1962  liquidData.Status = LIQUID_MAP_ABOVE_WATER;
1963  }
1964  }
1965  }
1966  }
1967 
1968  return liquidData;
1969 }

1983 float Map::GetWaterOrGroundLevel(uint32 phasemask, float x, float y, float z, float* ground /*= nullptr*/, bool /*swim = false*/, float collisionHeight) const
1984 {
1985  if (const_cast<Map*>(this)->GetGrid(x, y))
1986  {

2007 Transport* Map::GetTransportForPos(uint32 phase, float x, float y, float z, WorldObject* worldobject)
2008 {
2009  G3D::Vector3 v(x, y, z + 2.0f);
2010  G3D::Ray r(v, G3D::Vector3(0, 0, -1));
2011  for (TransportsContainer::const_iterator itr = _transports.begin(); itr != _transports.end(); ++itr)
2012  if ((*itr)->IsInWorld() && (*itr)->GetExactDistSq(x, y, z) < 75.0f * 75.0f && (*itr)->m_model)
2013  {
2014  float dist = 30.0f;
2015  bool hit = (*itr)->m_model->intersectRay(r, dist, false, phase);
2016  if (hit)
2017  return *itr;
2018  }
2019 
2020  if (worldobject)
2021  if (GameObject* staticTrans = worldobject->FindNearestGameObjectOfType(GAMEOBJECT_TYPE_TRANSPORT, 75.0f))
2022  if (staticTrans->m_model)
2023  {
2024  float dist = 10.0f;
2025  bool hit = staticTrans->m_model->intersectRay(r, dist, false, phase);
2026  if (hit)
2027  if (GetHeight(phase, x, y, z, true, 30.0f) < (v.z - dist + 1.0f))
2028  return staticTrans->ToTransport();
2029  }
2030 
2031  return nullptr;
2032 }

2034 float Map::GetHeight(float x, float y, float z, bool checkVMap /*= true*/, float maxSearchDist /*= DEFAULT_HEIGHT_SEARCH*/) const
2035 {
2036  // find raw .map surface under Z coordinates
2037  float mapHeight = VMAP_INVALID_HEIGHT_VALUE;
2038  float gridHeight = GetGridHeight(x, y);
2039  if (G3D::fuzzyGe(z, gridHeight - GROUND_HEIGHT_TOLERANCE))
2040  mapHeight = gridHeight;
2041 
2042  float vmapHeight = VMAP_INVALID_HEIGHT_VALUE;
2043  if (checkVMap)
2044  {
2045  VMAP::IVMapMgr* vmgr = VMAP::VMapFactory::createOrGetVMapMgr();
2046  vmapHeight = vmgr->getHeight(GetId(), x, y, z, maxSearchDist); // look from a bit higher pos to find the floor
2047  }
2048 
2049  // mapHeight set for any above raw ground Z or <= INVALID_HEIGHT
2050  // vmapheight set for any under Z value or <= INVALID_HEIGHT
2051  if (vmapHeight > INVALID_HEIGHT)
2052  {
2053  if (mapHeight > INVALID_HEIGHT)
2054  {
2055  // we have mapheight and vmapheight and must select more appropriate
2056 
2057  // we are already under the surface or vmap height above map heigt
2058  // or if the distance of the vmap height is less the land height distance
2059  if (vmapHeight > mapHeight || fabs(mapHeight - z) > fabs(vmapHeight - z))
2060  return vmapHeight;
2061  else
2062  return mapHeight; // better use .map surface height
2063  }
2064  else
2065  return vmapHeight; // we have only vmapHeight (if have)
2066  }
2067 
2068  return mapHeight; // explicitly use map data
2069 }

2615 void Map::AddObjectToSwitchList(WorldObject* obj, bool on)

2632 void Map::RemoveAllObjectsInRemoveList()
2633 {
2634  while (!i_objectsToSwitch.empty())
2635  {
2636  std::map<WorldObject*, bool>::iterator itr = i_objectsToSwitch.begin();
2637  WorldObject* obj = itr->first;
2638  bool on = itr->second;
2639  i_objectsToSwitch.erase(itr);
2640 
2641  if (!obj->IsPermanentWorldObject())
2642  {
2643  switch (obj->GetTypeId())
2644  {
2645  case TYPEID_UNIT:
2646  SwitchGridContainers<Creature>(obj->ToCreature(), on);
2647  break;
2648  case TYPEID_GAMEOBJECT:
2649  SwitchGridContainers<GameObject>(obj->ToGameObject(), on);
2650  break;
2651  default:
2652  break;
2653  }
2654  }
2655  }
2656 
2657  //LOG_DEBUG("maps", "Object remover 1 check.");
2658  while (!i_objectsToRemove.empty())
2659  {
2660  std::unordered_set<WorldObject*>::iterator itr = i_objectsToRemove.begin();
2661  WorldObject* obj = *itr;
2662  i_objectsToRemove.erase(itr);
2663 
2664  switch (obj->GetTypeId())
2665  {
2666  case TYPEID_CORPSE:
2667  {
2668  Corpse* corpse = ObjectAccessor::GetCorpse(*obj, obj->GetGUID());
2669  if (!corpse)
2670  LOG_ERROR("maps", "Tried to delete corpse/bones %s that is not in map.", obj->GetGUID().ToString().c_str());
2671  else
2672  RemoveFromMap(corpse, true);
2673  break;
2674  }
2675  case TYPEID_DYNAMICOBJECT:
2676  RemoveFromMap((DynamicObject*)obj, true);
2677  break;
2678  case TYPEID_GAMEOBJECT:
2679  if (MotionTransport* transport = obj->ToGameObject()->ToMotionTransport())
2680  RemoveFromMap(transport, true);
2681  else
2682  RemoveFromMap(obj->ToGameObject(), true);
2683  break;
2684  case TYPEID_UNIT:
2685  // in case triggered sequence some spell can continue casting after prev CleanupsBeforeDelete call
2686  // make sure that like sources auras/etc removed before destructor start
2687  obj->ToCreature()->CleanupsBeforeDelete();
2688  RemoveFromMap(obj->ToCreature(), true);
2689  break;
2690  default:
2691  LOG_ERROR("maps", "Non-grid object (TypeId: %u) is in grid object remove list, ignored.", obj->GetTypeId());
2692  break;
2693  }
2694  }
2695 
2696  //LOG_DEBUG("maps", "Object remover 2 check.");
2697 }

2829 /*
2830  Do map specific checks to see if the player can enter
2831 */
2832 Map::EnterState InstanceMap::CannotEnter(Player* player, bool loginCheck)
2833 {
2834  if (!loginCheck && player->GetMapRef().getTarget() == this)
2835  {
2836  LOG_ERROR("maps", "InstanceMap::CanEnter - player %s (%s) already in map %d, %d, %d!",
2837  player->GetName().c_str(), player->GetGUID().ToString().c_str(), GetId(), GetInstanceId(), GetSpawnMode());
2838 
2839  return CANNOT_ENTER_ALREADY_IN_MAP;
2840  }
2841 
2842  // allow GM's to enter
2843  if (player->IsGameMaster())
2844  return Map::CannotEnter(player, loginCheck);
2845 
2846  // cannot enter if the instance is full (player cap), GMs don't count
2847  uint32 maxPlayers = GetMaxPlayers();
2848  if (GetPlayersCountExceptGMs() >= (loginCheck ? maxPlayers + 1 : maxPlayers))
2849  {
2850  LOG_DEBUG("maps", "MAP: Instance '%u' of map '%s' cannot have more than '%u' players. Player '%s' rejected", GetInstanceId(), GetMapName(), maxPlayers, player->GetName().c_str());
2851  player->SendTransferAborted(GetId(), TRANSFER_ABORT_MAX_PLAYERS);
2852  return CANNOT_ENTER_MAX_PLAYERS;
2853  }
2854 
2855  // cannot enter while an encounter is in progress on raids
2856  bool checkProgress = (IsRaid() || GetId() == 668 /*HoR*/);
2857  if (checkProgress && GetInstanceScript() && GetInstanceScript()->IsEncounterInProgress())
2858  {
2859  player->SendTransferAborted(GetId(), TRANSFER_ABORT_ZONE_IN_COMBAT);
2860  return CANNOT_ENTER_ZONE_IN_COMBAT;
2861  }
2862 
2863  // xinef: dont allow LFG Group to enter other instance that is selected
2864  if (Group* group = player->GetGroup())
2865  if (group->isLFGGroup())
2866  if (!sLFGMgr->inLfgDungeonMap(group->GetGUID(), GetId(), GetDifficulty()))
2867  {
2868  player->SendTransferAborted(GetId(), TRANSFER_ABORT_MAP_NOT_ALLOWED);
2869  return CANNOT_ENTER_UNSPECIFIED_REASON;
2870  }
2871 
2872  // cannot enter if instance is in use by another party/soloer that have a permanent save in the same instance id
2873  PlayerList const& playerList = GetPlayers();
2874  if (!playerList.isEmpty())
2875  for (PlayerList::const_iterator i = playerList.begin(); i != playerList.end(); ++i)
2876  if (Player* iPlayer = i->GetSource())
2877  {
2878  if (iPlayer == player) // login case, player already added to map
2879  continue;
2880  if (iPlayer->IsGameMaster()) // bypass GMs
2881  continue;
2882  if (!player->GetGroup()) // player has not group and there is someone inside, deny entry
2883  {
2884  player->SendTransferAborted(GetId(), TRANSFER_ABORT_MAX_PLAYERS);
2885  return CANNOT_ENTER_INSTANCE_BIND_MISMATCH;
2886  }
2887  // player inside instance has no group or his groups is different to entering player's one, deny entry
2888  if (!iPlayer->GetGroup() || iPlayer->GetGroup() != player->GetGroup())
2889  {
2890  player->SendTransferAborted(GetId(), TRANSFER_ABORT_MAX_PLAYERS);
2891  return CANNOT_ENTER_INSTANCE_BIND_MISMATCH;
2892  }
2893  break;
2894  }
2895 
2896  return Map::CannotEnter(player, loginCheck);
2897 }

2899 /*
2900  Do map specific checks and add the player to the map if successful.
2901 */
2902 bool InstanceMap::AddPlayerToMap(Player* player)
2903 {
2904  if (m_resetAfterUnload) // this instance has been reset, it's not meant to be used anymore
2905  return false;
2906 
2907  if (IsDungeon())
2908  {
2909  Group* group = player->GetGroup();
2910 
2911  // get an instance save for the map
2912  InstanceSave* mapSave = sInstanceSaveMgr->GetInstanceSave(GetInstanceId());
2913  if (!mapSave)
2914  {
2915  LOG_ERROR("maps", "InstanceMap::Add: InstanceSave does not exist for map %d spawnmode %d with instance id %d", GetId(), GetSpawnMode(), GetInstanceId());
2916  return false;
2917  }
2918 
2919  // check for existing instance binds
2920  InstancePlayerBind* playerBind = sInstanceSaveMgr->PlayerGetBoundInstance(player->GetGUID(), GetId(), Difficulty(GetSpawnMode()));
2921  if (playerBind && playerBind->perm)
2922  {
2923  if (playerBind->save != mapSave)
2924  {
2925  LOG_ERROR("maps", "InstanceMap::Add: player %s (%s) is permanently bound to instance %d, %d, %d, %d but he is being put into instance %d, %d, %d, %d",
2926  player->GetName().c_str(), player->GetGUID().ToString().c_str(), playerBind->save->GetMapId(), playerBind->save->GetInstanceId(), playerBind->save->GetDifficulty(),
2927  playerBind->save->CanReset(), mapSave->GetMapId(), mapSave->GetInstanceId(), mapSave->GetDifficulty(), mapSave->CanReset());
2928  return false;
2929  }
2930  }
2931  else
2932  {
2933  playerBind = sInstanceSaveMgr->PlayerBindToInstance(player->GetGUID(), mapSave, false, player);
2934  // pussywizard: bind lider also if not yet bound
2935  if (Group* g = player->GetGroup())
2936  if (g->GetLeaderGUID() != player->GetGUID())
2937  if (!sInstanceSaveMgr->PlayerGetBoundInstance(g->GetLeaderGUID(), mapSave->GetMapId(), mapSave->GetDifficulty()))
2938  {
2939  sInstanceSaveMgr->PlayerCreateBoundInstancesMaps(g->GetLeaderGUID());
2940  sInstanceSaveMgr->PlayerBindToInstance(g->GetLeaderGUID(), mapSave, false, ObjectAccessor::FindConnectedPlayer(g->GetLeaderGUID()));
2941  }
2942  }
2943 
2944  // increase current instances (hourly limit)
2945  // xinef: specific instances are still limited
2946  if (!group || !group->isLFGGroup() || !group->IsLfgRandomInstance())
2947  player->AddInstanceEnterTime(GetInstanceId(), time(nullptr));
2948 
2949  if (!playerBind->perm && !mapSave->CanReset() && group && !group->isLFGGroup() && !group->IsLfgRandomInstance())
2950  {
2951  WorldPacket data(SMSG_INSTANCE_LOCK_WARNING_QUERY, 9);
2952  data << uint32(60000);
2953  data << uint32(instance_data ? instance_data->GetCompletedEncounterMask() : 0);
2954  data << uint8(0);
2955  player->GetSession()->SendPacket(&data);
2956  player->SetPendingBind(mapSave->GetInstanceId(), 60000);
2957  }
2958  }
2959 
2960  // initialize unload state
2961  m_unloadTimer = 0;
2962  m_resetAfterUnload = false;
2963  m_unloadWhenEmpty = false;
2964 
2965  // this will acquire the same mutex so it cannot be in the previous block
2966  Map::AddPlayerToMap(player);
2967 
2968  if (instance_data)
2969  instance_data->OnPlayerEnter(player);
2970 
2971  return true;
2972 }

3410 void Map::UpdateEncounterState(EncounterCreditType type, uint32 creditEntry, Unit* source)
3411 {
3412  Difficulty difficulty_fixed = (IsSharedDifficultyMap(GetId()) ? Difficulty(GetDifficulty() % 2) : GetDifficulty());
3413  DungeonEncounterList const* encounters;

3423

3425  {
3426  return;

3567 Corpse* Map::ConvertCorpseToBones(ObjectGuid const ownerGuid, bool insignia /*= false*/)

3813 bool Map::CanReachPositionAndGetValidCoords(const WorldObject* source, float startX, float startY, float startZ, float &destX, float &destY, float &destZ, bool failOnCollision, bool failOnSlopes) const
3814 {
3815  if (!CheckCollisionAndGetValidCoords(source, startX, startY, startZ, destX, destY, destZ, failOnCollision))
3816  {
3817  return false;
3818  }
3819 
3820  const Unit* unit = source->ToUnit();
3821  // if it's not an unit (Object) then we do not have to continue
3822  // with walkable checks
3823  if (!unit)
3824  {
3825  return true;
3826  }
3827 
3828  /*
3829  * Walkable checks
3830  */
3831  bool isWaterNext = HasEnoughWater(unit, destX, destY, destZ);
3832  const Creature* creature = unit->ToCreature();
3833  bool cannotEnterWater = isWaterNext && (creature && !creature->CanEnterWater());
3834  bool cannotWalkOrFly = !isWaterNext && !source->ToPlayer() && !unit->CanFly() && (creature && !creature->CanWalk());
3835  if (cannotEnterWater || cannotWalkOrFly ||
3836  (failOnSlopes && !PathGenerator::IsWalkableClimb(startX, startY, startZ, destX, destY, destZ, source->GetCollisionHeight())))
3837  {
3838  return false;
3839  }
3840 
3841  return true;
3842 }

3851 bool Map::CheckCollisionAndGetValidCoords(const WorldObject* source, float startX, float startY, float startZ, float &destX, float &destY, float &destZ, bool failOnCollision) const
3852 {
3853  // Prevent invalid coordinates here, position is unchanged
3854  if (!Acore::IsValidMapCoord(startX, startY, startZ) || !Acore::IsValidMapCoord(destX, destY, destZ))
3855  {
3856  LOG_FATAL("maps", "Map::CheckCollisionAndGetValidCoords invalid coordinates startX: %f, startY: %f, startZ: %f, destX: %f, destY: %f, destZ: %f", startX, startY, startZ, destX, destY, destZ);
3857  return false;
3858  }
3859 
3860  bool isWaterNext = IsInWater(source->GetPhaseMask(), destX, destY, destZ, source->GetCollisionHeight());
3861 
3862  PathGenerator path(source);
3863 
3864  // Use a detour raycast to get our first collision point
3865  path.SetUseRaycast(true);
3866  bool result = path.CalculatePath(startX, startY, startZ, destX, destY, destZ, false);
3867 
3868  const Unit* unit = source->ToUnit();
3869  bool notOnGround = path.GetPathType() & PATHFIND_NOT_USING_PATH
3870  || isWaterNext || (unit && unit->IsFlying());
3871 
3872  // Check for valid path types before we proceed
3873  if (!result || (!notOnGround && path.GetPathType() & ~(PATHFIND_NORMAL | PATHFIND_SHORTCUT | PATHFIND_INCOMPLETE | PATHFIND_FARFROMPOLY_END)))
3874  {
3875  return false;
3876  }
3877 
3878  G3D::Vector3 endPos = path.GetPath().back();
3879  destX = endPos.x;
3880  destY = endPos.y;
3881  destZ = endPos.z;
3882 
3883  // collision check
3884  bool collided = false;
3885 
3886  // check static LOS
3887  float halfHeight = source->GetCollisionHeight() * 0.5f;
3888 
3889  // Unit is not on the ground, check for potential collision via vmaps
3890  if (notOnGround)
3891  {
3892  bool col = VMAP::VMapFactory::createOrGetVMapMgr()->GetObjectHitPos(source->GetMapId(),
3893  startX, startY, startZ + halfHeight,
3894  destX, destY, destZ + halfHeight,
3895  destX, destY, destZ, -CONTACT_DISTANCE);
3896 
3897  destZ -= halfHeight;
3898 
3899  // Collided with static LOS object, move back to collision point
3900  if (col)
3901  {
3902  collided = true;
3903  }
3904  }
3905 
3906  // check dynamic collision
3907  bool col = source->GetMap()->GetObjectHitPos(source->GetPhaseMask(),
3908  startX, startY, startZ + halfHeight,
3909  destX, destY, destZ + halfHeight,
3910  destX, destY, destZ, -CONTACT_DISTANCE);
3911 
3912  destZ -= halfHeight;
3913 
3914  // Collided with a gameobject, move back to collision point
3915  if (col)
3916  {
3917  collided = true;
3918  }
3919 
3920  float groundZ = VMAP_INVALID_HEIGHT_VALUE;
3921  source->UpdateAllowedPositionZ(destX, destY, destZ, &groundZ);
3922 
3923  // position has no ground under it (or is too far away)
3924  if (groundZ <= INVALID_HEIGHT && unit && !unit->CanFly())
3925  {
3926  // fall back to gridHeight if any
3927  float gridHeight = GetGridHeight(destX, destY);
3928  if (gridHeight > INVALID_HEIGHT)
3929  {
3930  destZ = gridHeight + unit->GetHoverHeight();
3931  }
3932  else
3933  {
3934  return false;
3935  }
3936  }
3937 
3938  return !failOnCollision || !collided;
3939 }
